    <description>&lt;h2&gt;Magemall AjaxLogin&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;
    &lt;p&gt;Magemall AjaxLogin will replace the login link to an ajax popup box.It's easy to use without any core code change.&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;
&lt;ol&gt;&#xD;
&lt;li&gt;After you downloading, unzip the file and upload to your magento website directory.&lt;/li&gt;&#xD;
&lt;li&gt;Go to the System -&amp;gt; Cache Management, Refresh all the caches. .&lt;/li&gt;&#xD;
&lt;li&gt;Go to the System -&amp;gt; Configuration, and a new tab Magemall -&amp;gt; Magemall AjaxLogin should be added in the left menu. &amp;nbsp;Click it.&lt;/li&gt;&#xD;
&lt;li&gt;Enable it (See figure-1). If you got a 404 page, please re-login&amp;nbsp;your account and try again.&lt;/li&gt;&#xD;
&lt;li&gt;Come back to your frontend page and click "Login". It should be popup an ajax login box.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;(See figure-1).&lt;/li&gt;&#xD;
&lt;li&gt;All done. Enjoy it.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/ol&gt;&#xD;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;
&lt;p&gt;Finger:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;
&lt;img src="http://magento.luochunhui.com/docs/imgs/ajaxlogin/ajaxlogin.png" alt=""&gt;&#xD;
